.jumbotron
  .container
    %h1 TODO list(s)
    %p
      This example shows how to create a TODO list and use bigbang to
      handle events like adding an item, removing an item, and setting
      the items.

- [0,1].each do |x|
  .row
    - [0,1].each do |y|
      .col-md-6
        .panel.panel-default.todo{ id: "todo-#{2*x+y}" }
          %table.table.table-striped.table-bordered.table-hover.todo-items
          .panel-body
            %form.todo-controls
              .input-group
                %input.form-control.todo-text{ type: 'text' }
                .input-group-btn
                  %button.btn.btn-primary.todo-add
                    \ Add
                  %button.btn.btn-primary.todo-send
                    \ Send
%pre
  %code&= File.read 'views/coffee/todolist.coffee'
